OL,3,CDid the King just deliver the verbal
OL,4,Cequivalent of burning down the White
OL,5,CHouse?
OL,7,FFor a King who's had decades of
OL,8,Ftraining in diplomacy, his speech to
OL,9,Fthe US Congress on Tuesday turned out
OL,10,Fto be much more spiky than many had
OL,11,Fpredicted.
OL,13,FGiven the British government had
OL,14,Fdispatched King Charles and Queen
OL,15,FCamilla to patch up what was left of
OL,16,Fthe transatlantic relationship, the
OL,17,Fcharm offensive turned into something
OL,18,Fof a push back against everything
OL,19,FDonald Trump had been saying about the
OL,20,FUK in the previous weeks.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G1/14
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,319,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31802
SC,0002
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F318A1777471868
OL,3,CDid the King just deliver the verbal
OL,4,Cequivalent of burning down the White
OL,5,CHouse?
OL,7,FBe it on Ukraine, or NATO, on
OL,8,Fsupporting the USA after 9/11, on
OL,9,Fkeeping executive power in check, or
OL,10,Fon the melting ice caps ("climate
OL,11,Fchange" was clearly considered a
OL,12,Fphrase too far), the address on
OL,13,FCapitol Hill wasn't short on news.
OL,15,FBut as he became the first King ever
OL,16,Fto speak to a joint session of the US
OL,17,FCongress (his mother was the first
OL,18,FBritish Monarch to do so in 1991),
OL,19,FCharles delivered the blows in a soft
OL,20,Fand gentle style and even managed to
OL,21,Fcharm his audience as he did so.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G2/14
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,319,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31803
SC,0003
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F318A1777471868
OL,3,CDid the King just deliver the verbal
OL,4,Cequivalent of burning down the White
OL,5,CHouse?
OL,7,FHe began by offering America his
OL,8,Fsupport following the shooting attempt
OL,9,Fat the weekend.
OL,11,F"Let me say with unshakeable resolve:
OL,12,Fsuch acts of violence will never
OL,13,Fsucceed", the King said.
OL,15,F"Whatever our differences, whatever
OL,16,Fdisagreements we may have, we stand
OL,17,Funited in our commitment to uphold
OL,18,Fdemocracy".
OL,26,@uD@HO]zD@JO]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G3/14
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,319,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31804
SC,0004
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F318A1777471868
OL,3,CDid the King just deliver the verbal
OL,4,Cequivalent of burning down the White
OL,5,CHouse?
OL,7,FHe joked that he was not here to claim
OL,8,Fback the country, as he referenced his
OL,9,Ffive-times great grandfather, George
OL,10,FIII, who was the last King of America.
OL,12,FEveryone on both sides of the Atlantic
OL,13,Fwill agree that UK-US relations are
OL,14,Fbetter today than they were in 1776,
OL,15,Feven after the verbal mauling Donald
OL,16,FTrump has unleashed on the British
OL,17,Fmilitary and the British Prime
OL,18,FMinister in recent weeks.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G4/14
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,319,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31805
SC,0005
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F318A1777471868
OL,3,CDid the King just deliver the verbal
OL,4,Cequivalent of burning down the White
OL,5,CHouse?
OL,7,F"With the Spirit of 1776 in our minds,
OL,8,Fwe can perhaps agree that we do not
OL,9,Falways agree ` at least in the first
OL,10,Finstance!", was how the King dispensed
OL,11,Fwith the British defeat in the
OL,12,FAmerican War of Independence.
OL,14,FAnd with both Houses of Congress
OL,15,Fsufficiently charmed, the King quietly
OL,16,Fdispatched a series of messages which,
OL,17,Fhad they been delivered by a
OL,18,Fpolitician, might have caused an
OL,19,FAmerican War of Diplomacy.
OL,26,@rD@JO]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G5/14
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,319,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31806
SC,0006
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F318A1777471868
OL,3,CDid the King just deliver the verbal
OL,4,Cequivalent of burning down the White
OL,5,CHouse?
OL,7,FThe Founding Fathers, said the King,
OL,8,Fwere "bold and imaginative rebels" who
OL,9,Fcarried with them ideals from the
OL,10,FMagna Carta, not least "the foundation
OL,11,Fof the principle that executive power
OL,12,Fis subject to checks and balances."
OL,14,FIt was a powerful reminder in front of
OL,15,FUS lawmakers of the attempts by the
OL,16,FWhite House to stretch the limits of
OL,17,Fits democratic mandate over this
OL,18,Fnation's legislature and judiciary.
OL,26,@pD@FOUpD@bO]tD@cO]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G6/14
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
