OL,3,CDid the King just deliver the verbal
OL,4,Cequivalent of burning down the White
OL,5,CHouse?
OL,7,FSubscribe free to our weekly
OL,8,Fnewsletter for exclusive and original
OL,9,Fcoverage from ITV News. Direct to your
OL,10,Finbox every Friday morning.
OL,12,FHe used the word "shared" nine times
OL,13,Fand received 12 standing ovations.
OL,15,FBut as the speech went on, the return
OL,16,Fpunches kept coming.
OL,18,FThis is a "more volatile and more
OL,19,Fdangerous" era than the world of which
OL,20,Fhis late mother spoke in this same
OL,21,Fchamber in 1991.
OL,26,@tD@ROUtD@YO]{D@JO]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G7/14
