OL,3,CDid the King just deliver the verbal
OL,4,Cequivalent of burning down the White
OL,5,CHouse?
OL,7,FThe ice caps are "disastrously
OL,8,Fmelting", nature must be "safeguarded"
OL,9,Fand "we ignore at our peril," said the
OL,10,FKing, the collapse of natural systems
OL,11,Fwhich "provide the foundation for our
OL,12,Fprosperity and our national security.
OL,14,F"Climate change" are two words that
OL,15,Fappear in most of the King's speeches
OL,16,Fbut it was clearly decided this phrase
OL,17,Fwould be a provocation too far.
OL,19,FAnd just as he was wrapping things up,
OL,20,Fa warning that the Make America Great
OL,21,FAgain movement should know its limits.
OL,26,@oD@ROUpD@ZOUpD@fO]qD@EOUvD@AOUvD@PO]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                   G12/14
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,319,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31813
SC,0013
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F318A1777471868
OL,3,CDid the King just deliver the verbal
OL,4,Cequivalent of burning down the White
OL,5,CHouse?
OL,7,F"I pray with all my heart that our
OL,8,FAlliance will continue to defend our
OL,9,Fshared values, with our partners in
OL,10,FEurope and the Commonwealth, and
OL,11,Facross the world, and that we ignore
OL,12,Fthe clarion calls to become ever more
OL,13,Finward-looking."
OL,15,FIf it hadn't been delivered by King
OL,16,FCharles, this speech might have been
OL,17,Fconsidered the verbal equivalent of
OL,18,Fthe British burning down the White
OL,19,FHouse in 1814.
OL,26,@uD@PO]
